## Incomplete Certificate Chains

In some cases, a %server or %client may send an incomplete certificate chain, 
where the last certificate in the chain (the root certificate) is missing. In 
those instances, @moc_platform makes appropriate calls to hookup 
functions that you define in your application. Those hookup functions then 
complete the chain and verification by using the certificates found in a trusted 
certificate store.

